Red Sand Accounts field agents have expanded operations beyond their chartered zones and are now intercepting bonded caravans registered with Kowloon trade houses in Warden patrol territory. The debt collectors, assessors, and enforcers work in coordinated units that cannot be engaged one at a time. The Kowloon postmaster requires elimination of one agent from each tier to collapse the current operational cell and force a Red Sand withdrawal from the contested zone.
The Red Sand Accounts field cell operating in the Warden patrol zone has been neutralized. Bonded caravans registered with Kowloon trade houses are reporting uncontested passage through the previously interdicted section. The postmaster has forwarded a territorial boundary protest to Red Sand Accounts headquarters citing the engagement data.

